positive type, negative type, negative&nbsp;
type. To determine the type of the sum,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:04.020 --> 00:11:08.100
okay, which is going to be another zero,&nbsp;
but what kind of zero, what type of zero,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:08.100 --> 00:11:16.500
we just form the product of all these types. Okay,&nbsp;
and well, that's going to be negative because&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:22.440
there is an odd number of negatives. So you get a&nbsp;
negative, and that means that the resulting sum is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:33.480
an anti-box or anti-zero in red. Okay, the crucial&nbsp;
annihilation creation sort of property that we&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:33.480 --> 00:11:40.920
insist that objects and anti-objects have is that&nbsp;
if we have a box, capital B, and its anti-box,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:42.060 --> 00:11:51.840
BA, B super A, or anti-B, if they both occur&nbsp;
in a box, a capital B box M, okay, then they&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:59.220
